When they came to Capernaum, those who collected the two drachmas came to Peter and said, "Doesn't your teacher pay the two drachmas?"
He said, "Yes." When he entered the house, Jesus spoke first, "What do you think, Simon? From whom do the kings of the earth collect duty and tribute, from their own children or from others?"
Peter said to him, "From strangers." Jesus said to him, "Then the sons are free."
But lest we find them, go to the sea and cast a line, and the first fish that comes up take it, and when you open its mouth you will find a veil, take it and give it to them from me and from you."
